        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 4:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles northeast of Peyton to near Calhan.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Calhan, Ramah, and Peyton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
